  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency response for the people affected by Flood in Kasenyi and Tshomia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project aims to support the most vulnerable people - who in large proportion have settled unsheltered in public places and in the neighbourhood house accommodation  , with unconditional cash transfer aimed at providing in particular nonfood items( NFI) which comprised with wash kit assistance and emergency items  for the most vulnerable people with a special need (Older people, breastfeeding women, pregnant women, non-accompany children, disable people and people with chronic diseases) who are unsheltered.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, critical protection risks will be addressed, the living conditions of the of vulnerable groups (particularly the unsheltered people) will be improved and risk of disease outbreak will be immediately reduced as soon as cash distribution will be done and moderated within 45 days. All food-assisted households cover their food needs according to their habits and / or preferences and cover their needs in Shelter and non-food items.  At the end of this project, the beneficiary households will be able to purchase  NFIs for their households to meet their urgent needs in terms of food for the first 15 days and non-food items. HelpAge will provid wash assitance for the covid prevention and the water born diseases.</narrative>
  </description>
